t_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["The GDP of W is 14\n","The GDP of C is 12.970000000000002\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Question 3: Economic Impact Calculator\n","\n","Create a function `calculate_impact` to estimate the economic impact of a new policy in a country. The function should:\n","\n","1. Accept three inputs:\n","   - `gdp_growth`: expected GDP growth rate (float)\n","   - `unemployment_rate`: current unemployment rate (float)\n","   - `is_tax_cut`: whether the policy includes a tax cut (boolean)\n","\n","2. Return the estimated economic impact as a float.\n","\n","Use the following assumptions:\n","- Base economic impact (with 0% GDP growth, 0% unemployment, no tax cut): 1000\n","- Each percentage point of GDP growth: +500\n","- Each percentage point of unemployment: -300\n","- Tax cut: +2000\n","\n","Examples:\n","- With 2% GDP growth, 5% unemployment, no tax cut: 1600\n","  Calculation: 1000 + (2 × 500) - (5 × 300) = 1600\n","- With 3% GDP growth, 4% unemployment, with tax cut: 3100\n","  Calculation: 1000 + (3 × 500) - (4 × 300) + 2000 = 3100\n","\n","Write the function and test it with:\n","```python\n","calculate_impact(2, 5, False)\n","calculate_impact(3, 4, True)\n","```\n"],"metadata":{"id":"u2KTJqJ-EMHN"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# [Your answer]\n","\n","def calculate_impact(gdp_growth, unemployment_rate, is_tax_cut):\n","  impact_base = 1000\n","  impact_gdp_growth = gdp_growth * 500\n","  impact_unemployment_rate = -unemployment_rate * 300\n","  impact_is_tax_cut = is_tax_cut * 2000\n","  impact_total = impact_gdp_growth + impact_unemployment_rate + impact_is_tax_cut + impact_base\n","  return(impact_total)\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"iqhAsQgz6dfr","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1770516435756,"user_tz":-480,"elapsed":6,"user":{"displayName":"Victoria Kobzeva","userId":"00262820123580309343"}}},"execution_count":236,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["calculate_impact(2, 5, False)"],"metadata":